			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I tried here at 46.  Used Focused Air pet, full summoned armor, weapons, etc (as available for my level).  No KEI, started with C2, but it ran out too soon. Oh well. Sat outside pyramid, buffed pet with BO2 and Damage Shield.  All that i did was (after a few test pulls) just hit F8 to target ANY skelly in Line of Sight, and right clicked my White Ceramic Band for a 5 pt DD hit.  Even if the mob I had target had moved out of sight before I clicked, the mob was pulled.  Single, EVERY time. 
<br />

<br />
The mobs walk a regular path within the pyramid, in a square from your right to left, then into the back of the room on the left, then left to right in the back, then back to front right.  Often many will "clump" together in a corner of that pathing, and I was able to target one in a clump and pull a single, even though there are 2-5 mobs at the same exact spot.
<br />

<br />
I was able to clear the room and space out the mobsfairly evenly.  I didnt try to keep the population down, since assisting mobs was not a problem.  
<br />

<br />
BEST ADVICE I can give:  Be patient and WAIT for the mobs to walk across your line of sight in front of the entrance.  You CAN target them if they are way out in the back, but you will have to move close to entrance for the White Ceramic Band to successfully cast.  This is how I got my 2 multiple mob aggros.
<br />

<br />
Because I had stepped into the entrance a little too much to pull ones at the back, the sudden appearance of a mob walking across the front entrance drew aggro. Essentially - Right and Left Front corners of that room are blind spots for you, unless you use different camera angles to compensate.  I was lazy and didn't.  I did manage to Kite the extra mob, but each time lost pet in the process.  I have Jboots so speed was not an issue. (Kite in this case = Run, get enough space between me and mob to cast a nuke in time to land and run some more, repeat.)  I didnt keep an AE spell mem'd - didnt need it for the single pulls.
<br />

<br />
----------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
Side note: 
<br />

<br />
I found that the groups that I had been getting in DL near KC fort had good players playing this week and pullers who KNEW how to keep a steady chain pull going, so I went back to grouping. The XP was MUCH faster and constant.  For example - I played 10 hours yesterday from level 46 (1 yellow and less than 1 blue) to 48 (+1 yellow in) and had 4 pullers come and go - 3 were excellent chain pullers.  With KEI I often got LOM but the melees took up the slack and killed fast. Without KEI I just paced my nukes and Elemental DOT carefully. Best XP was when a 48 Wizzy joined us and we worked out a 1-2 punch.  He was hitting for 1110 and I was hitting for 600+ on mobs.  We had it down to the 2 nukes hitting within les than 1 second. The mobs would then be low enough to start their feeble attempt at fleeing.  Everyone began to complain and tell us to give the melees a chance to kill, and we offered to use lower nukes.  The response was unanimously "NO WAY - KEEP GOING".
<br />

<br />
Just goes to show - in a group Mages need to work with others to make yourself effective in assisting in the kill.  Make your mage effective and useful and people will start thinking a lot better about us and wanting to include us instead of vilifying us as useless.  We are a very flexible class, and CAN fit in very well with groups. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
Character: Iniaru L'Amantirre
<br />
Magician , 48th Element
<br />
Innoruuk Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
