				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did this camp for a few hours today at 48... used focused water pet with the usual goodies, BOII and DS. Was pretty straightforward, got 60% of the level with no danger at all, really. I'd like to add a few things though...
<br />

<br />
1) Facing the way into the pyramid, sit back and to the RIGHT. There is a wandering skeleton spawn that will walk all the way over the pyramid and then down the side to the left of the entrance. 
<br />

<br />
2) Instead of using F8 or waiting for them to walk across doorway, I suggest using Eye of Zomm to target a skel inside and then pull right through the wall. Just use your Clay Bracelet (unlimited charges of instant cast Eye of Zomm). If you don't have one yet, go quest for one, it's easily soloed in a matter of hours (can be done in under an hour if you're lucky with the spawns) by any mage high lvl enough to do this camp. And it's NODROP (both the item and the quest pieces) so you won't find people farming it or anything.
<br />

<br />
3) A named might wander across nearby... the Wraithbone Champion. I don't suggest trying him until you're at LEAST 49... He was blue at 48, so I tried him with a fully healed/buffed pet and 80% mana (I have 222 INT and +235 mana), and was owned rather nicely. Didn't resist much, Malisement stuck on first try and DDs did close to full dmg, but has a LOT more HP than the thieves and hits harder (doubles for about 120). I tried chain heal/DDing and only got him down to 40% before my pet was dying and I was at 10% mana... needless to say, I gated, and by the time I got back someone else had taken the camp. If you have 49 pet, he might be doable with chain nuke/heal, but otherwise I suggest leaving him alone.
<br />

<br />
Edit: This camp becomes a laugher at 49. Focused 49 fire pet with all the goodies pretty much kills a skel by himself. I didn't even nuke, just pulled with Band for the exp and tossed it 1 heal per fight. I was clearing the spawns so easily (with no additional mana regen of any kind) that I also started killing the two wanderers that cross the pyramid and the Brother Balatin spawn on the small pyramid to the left and behind the thief pyramid. Balatin is very green, but his PH greater plaguebones are very solidly blue (seem a bit tougher than the thieves but not much). Did all of 49 in right about what the subject says, 3.5 - 4 hours.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=869368" target="_blank" class="postlink">Succor</a>
<br />
54 Erudite Elementalist
<br />
Povar</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
